#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.41:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.41:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Dārukkhandhasutta"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an6.41:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr ""

#. </span>
msgctxt "an6.41:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""

# BB has"block of wood. But I think Sariputta saw something like this: https://www.google.com/search?q=fallen+tree+trunk&tbm=isch Not something like this: https://www.google.com/search?q=block+of+wood&tbm=isch
msgctxt "an6.41:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasa "
"aññatarasmiṃ padese mahantaṃ dārukkhandhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:1.4"
msgid "Disvā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:1.5"
msgid "“passatha no, āvuso, tumhe amuṃ mahantaṃ dārukkhandhan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:1.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr ""

# I think BB’s “might focus on as earth” is too weak. It’s no great feat to focus on a specific aspect of things and tune other aspects out. I can do it. Heck, anyone who gets absorbed in a TV show does it. Surely this means something rather more dramatic. Else why does it take a monk who is master of psychic powers? CPD has “to make a (magical) act of volition”, and while I would disagree that it’s magical, it’s at least getting there.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.341"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.41:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Ākaṅkhamāno, āvuso, bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto amuṃ dārukkhandhaṃ "
"pathavītveva adhimucceyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atthi, āvuso, amumhi dārukkhandhe pathavīdhātu, yaṃ nissāya bhikkhu iddhimā "
"cetovasippatto amuṃ dārukkhandhaṃ pathavītveva adhimucceyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ākaṅkhamāno, āvuso, bhikkhu iddhimā cetovasippatto amuṃ dārukkhandhaṃ "
"āpotveva adhimucceyya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.5"
msgid "tejotveva adhimucceyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.6"
msgid "vāyotveva adhimucceyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.7"
msgid "subhantveva adhimucceyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.8"
msgid "asubhantveva adhimucceyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.41:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

# I think this is the only case where subhadhatu and asubhadhatu are used. Overall, the text feels a little late. Vulture’s Peak soon became associated with the mystical.
msgctxt "an6.41:2.10"
msgid ""
"Atthi, āvuso, amumhi dārukkhandhe asubhadhātu, yaṃ nissāya bhikkhu iddhimā "
"cetovasippatto amuṃ dārukkhandhaṃ asubhantveva adhimucceyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.41:2.11"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
